#: ../../reference/directives.md:57
msgid "Scoped Begin / End"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:59
msgid ""
"The `lang-check-begin` / `lang-check-end` directives define scoped "
"regions with richer options than basic disable/enable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:68
msgid "An unclosed `lang-check-begin` extends to the end of the file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:70
msgid "Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:72
msgid "Options are space-separated tokens after `lang-check-begin`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:74
msgid "Rule IDs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:76
msgid ""
"Bare tokens (not matching any option prefix) are treated as rule IDs. "
"Only those rules are suppressed within the region:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:85
msgid ""
"With no rule IDs and no language override, all diagnostics in the region "
"are suppressed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:88
msgid "Language Override (`lang:xx`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:90
msgid ""
"Override the natural language for the region. The checker uses this "
"language instead of the document default. Takes precedence over `<!-- "
"lang: xx -->` scope markers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:100
msgid ""
"A region with **only** a `lang:` option (no rule IDs) acts as a pure "
"language override — it does not suppress any diagnostics."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:103
msgid "Line Slice (`check[a:b]`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:105
msgid ""
"Auto-close the region using slice notation. No `lang-check-end` is "
"needed. `a` and `b` are 0-indexed line offsets after the directive (like "
"Python slicing):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:117
msgid ""
"`check[:5]` covers lines 0–4 (the first 5 lines). You can also start from"
" an offset — `check[2:5]` would cover only lines 2–4:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:120
msgid "Match Filter (`match:/PATTERN/`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:122
msgid "Only apply the directive to lines matching the given regex:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:131
msgid "Exclude Filter (`exclude:/PATTERN/`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:133
msgid ""
"Skip lines matching the given regex — the directive does not apply to "
"them:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:142
msgid "Type Override (`type:FORMAT`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:144
msgid ""
"Re-parse the region using a different tree-sitter grammar. The content "
"inside the region is extracted as if it were a standalone document of the"
" specified format:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference/directives.md:154
msgid ""
"The format must be a supported language ID (e.g. `latex`, `html`, `rst`, "
"`org`). Unknown formats are skipped with a warning."
msgstr ""

